97
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,720
Please take a break at least.

98
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:33,240
Get out of here so I can finish this running.

99
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:35,200
Then, I’m gonna run with you.

100
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,120
Kongpob!

101
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:39,760
What the hell are you doing here?

102
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,640
I said get out!

103
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,600
No.

104
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,840
If you don’t stop, I won’t stop.

105
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,320
Kongpob!

106
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,320
Hey, Arthit.

107
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,520
What’s going on?

108
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,280
Get this brat out.

109
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,200
So I can continue running.

110
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:58,800
You, the first year,

111
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,040
what are you doing here?

112
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,640
He’s been running all day long already.

113
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,760
Why does he have to keep running?

114
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,640
But this is the punishment of the hazing team leader.

115
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,680
It’s not something for a first year like you to concern.

116
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:14,680
But I…

117
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,800
No more talking.

118
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,280
I don’t give you permission

119
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,560
Go wait over there.

120
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,680
Nong Kong.

121
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,080
Go up there and sit with your friends.

122
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,360
I’ll bring you some drink.

123
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,600
Hey, Kong.

124
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,760
Over here, have a seat.

125
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,520
We just finished our papers from the library.

126
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,960
When we saw that P’Arthit is still running,

127
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,640
we are here to watch.

128
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:27,440
I just shared his pic on the faculty’s web board.

129
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:29,280
It got reposted many of times.

130
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,200
How come you are here by the way?

131
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:34,200
M called and told me about this.

132
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:36,040
So I rushed to here.

133
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:40,800
I also heard it from the web board.

134
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,800
He completed 100 push ups.

135
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:54,080
100 squats

136
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,800
and 100 sits and stands.

137
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,960
I can’t help falling for this kind of guy

138
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,080
Give me a break.

139
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:09,200
You have soft spot for every man, Maprang.

140
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,760
I really like this senior-junior atmosphere.

141
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,360
Hey, Arthit

142
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,160
It’s the last lap already.

143
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,800
You are almost there.

144
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,520
Get up, man.

145
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:08,680
It’s all right.

146
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,320
You can do it, Arthit.

147
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,200
Get up, man. Get up.

148
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:19,160
It’s all right, man.

149
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,560
You are almost there.

150
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,240
You can do it, Arthit.

151
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,520
You don’t need to say anything.

152
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,840
We’re taking you to the doctor.

153
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,960
Are you all right, P’Arthit?

154
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,720
You’re not going back yet?

155
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,400
Go home.

156
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:04,800
Stay out of this.

157
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,560
It’s none of the first years’ business.

158
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,640
Let me take you to the hospital too.

159
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:10,960
Leave me alone.

160
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,240
Didn’t you hear me?

161
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:14,200
I said it was none of the first years’ business

162
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:18,320
This first year doesn’t have the right to worry about the third year like you?

163
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,760
Let’s get going, Knot.

164
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:29,360
I don’t want to keep this on

165
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,360
And for you,

166
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,960
This is the last warning from me.

167
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:37,240
Don’t ever meddle with the seniors’ matter.

168
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:39,240
Otherwise,

169
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,400
I punish the whole first-year class because of you.

170
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,760
Leave him alone, Kong.

171
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:27,760
I, myself, was not into this initiation ritual

172
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:29,400
I never wanted to join the gathering at my own will.

173
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:31,200
But if you take a good look at it,

174
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,360
this freshman gathering is just a creation of situations

175
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:36,160
It urges us to learn how to get through difficulties together in a team.

176
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,600
It’s like a library of experiences…

177
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,520
…where you can choose which experience you would like to read

178
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:44,080
The signature book makes me socialize more.

179
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,160
And the nametag…

180
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,680
That reminds me to think

181
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:49,480
and value the importance of knowing others

182
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:51,680
The attention I have to every small matter…

183
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:54,680
gives me the courage to raise my hand and help others.

184
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,920
These are the things I receive from the freshman gathering.

185
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,880
Though I know everything is just a set-up

186
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:01,720
But the role we play is real,

187
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,080
the pain is real,

188
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,720
and our hurtful feelings is also real.

189
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:08,200
Those seniors have put themselves out for us, the first years.

190
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,960
“P’Deer”

191
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,400
Prem.

192
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,040
Son of a b*, Prem!

193
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:37,920
What?

194
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:38,920
Get me the phone.

195
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,200
Get it yourself.

196
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,400
I can only move my lips and yell at you, you fool.

197
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,040
Get it for me.

198
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,040
All right

199
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:50,280
Sometimes, I wonder if I’m your friend or your servant.

200
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,360
Hello, P’Deer.

201
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,560
Hello. How are you holding up, bro?

202
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,320
Dead yet?

203
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,600
Almost actually.

204
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,880
I think I saw my late grandpa waving his hand for me.

205
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:07,040
I almost went to him, you know?

206
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,880
You can back talk like this,

207
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:10,480
I guess you are okay now.

208
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,880
Knot said he took you to the hospital

209
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,720
So I got worried.

210
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,880
I didn’t tell you to go overboard.

211
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:19,480
Didn’t we agree at just 20 laps?

212
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,000
Come on, bro.

213
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,360
I want to show those freshmen how powerful you are.

214
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,760
Powerful my ass.

215
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,760
It’s you who gets all the credits.

216
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:31,000
Many first years keep sharing the picture of you all over my Facebook.

217
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,200
They also bashed me for being too barbarian on you.

218
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:38,360
Come on. Just take it as my year to shine.

219
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,600
Okay. Get well soon, you fool.

220
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:41,680
Yes. Thank you.

221
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,560
You indeed exerted yourself too much.

222
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,160
It’s a rule after all.

223
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:51,440
Screw the rule. We are all in trouble because of that.

224
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,960
Prem, I’m hungry.

225
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,320
Go buy me congee.

226
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,200
Here you are.

227
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,680
Not this.

228
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:03,920
I want to drink pink milk too.

229
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:04,840
Hurry up.

230
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,640
I don’t want to go down.

231
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:07,880
Come on!

232
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:13,120
Don’t go too long, you jackass.

233
00:17:13,120 --> 00:17:14,160
The ice could get melted fast.

234
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,040
Money?

235
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:17,880
Come on, pay for me

236
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,880
Why? I want money.

237
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,000
I’ll pay later

238
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,520
I won’t lock the door.

239
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:23,360
Fine

240
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,760
Can I get a pink milk?

241
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:35,960
Certainly.

242
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:42,920
20 baht

243
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:45,320
Woah.

244
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:47,680
You have some lovely taste of a drink.

245
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:50,160
Sawasdee krup, P’Prem.

246
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:54,640
Do you buy this pink milk for yourself?

247
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,080
Why do you want to know?

248
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,880
Nothing actually.

249
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:04,680
Hello.

250
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:07,600
Take it easy. Is anything wrong?

251
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:16,160
I’ll be right there.

252
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,640
You do know that my leg hurts.

253
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,840
Why bother to knock on the door?

254
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:46,000
Get in. The door is not locked.

255
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,240
What took you so damn long?

256
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:04,480
Did you help them stir the congee pot or something?

257
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,840
Get it to me fast. I’m starving.

258
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,440
Excuse me.

259
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,280
Hello, you asshole.

260
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,160
Hold on. I’m not done yet.

261
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,240
Where the hell are you?

262
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,120
Playing game?

263
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,800
Put it on automatic, you fool.

264
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,200
Hello?

265
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:36,480
Come on. How could you be so busy all the damn time?

266
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,360
Oh, it’s you, dad.

267
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:43,400
Yeah, I’m still busy here. I have a match to compete this evening.

268
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:44,760
Yes, dad.

269
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,000
Yes, very exhausted, dad.

270
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,280
I’ve got to go now, dad.

271
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:49,320
All right. I love you.

272
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:50,720
Yes. Yes. Yes. See you.

273
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,760
